{
  "text": "Thus, a major physiological role for Zn 2+ may be the modulation of cell signaling cascades, especially those involving protein phosphorylation, and considering also that intracellular Zn 2+ can rise quickly and can influence Ca 2+ regulation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the relative very low abundance of Zn 2+ in cardiomyocytes suggests its availability as second messengers for gene expression [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . In an early study, Atar et al. [CITATION_5] showed that external Zn 2+ could activate gene expression in GH3 cells due to modification of expression of Zn",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "20022894",
